{
  "texts": [
    "Addressing this gap could substantially boost the functionality of data management systems, especially in complex and dataintensive IoMT.",
    "C. Contract Theory for Data SharingContract theory is a branch of economics that studies how contractual arrangements can be designed to align incentives between parties with asymmetric information [24], and it has been widely used in wireless communication, AI, and other fields [16], [24].",
    "In the context of data sharing, information asymmetry often arises because data holders possess more information about the data than data users.",
    "Contract theory can effectively incentivize data sharing by ensuring that both parties benefit from the exchange [16].",
    "For example, the authors in [25] proposed a two-period incentive mechanism for healthcare applications, which takes into account the Willingness To Participate (WTP) of users and satisfies intertemporal incentive compatibility."
  ]
}